reviewText: There are often occasions where seeing a live performance of a band you like is disappointing. This concert DVD is just the opposite. Not only does it confirm my belief that Keane are one of the best new artists around, it gave me a new found respect for them. I was a bit worried near the beginning of the performance because it seemed like Tom Chaplin might be getting into a bit of the self indulgent crowd interaction too much but I think after he calmed down the band concentrated on a great performance. And it was great. Chaplin's voice was absolutely solid. The sound quality is perfect. A fine mix despite the fact that it's only 3 guys and often just 2 making the music. The visuals are fantastic. It's really a pleasure to see that Keane has people that understand that lighting and visual effects add so much to a good concert. This DVD is an absolute must for Keane fans and anyone else that appreciates great new music performed by seriously talented individuals.

reviewText: I love KEANE first of all BUT the way this concert is filmed and recorded is far superior to most modern concert or DVD/BLU-RAY releases.  The closest thing I own is the recent POLICE reunion BLU-RAY.  This is Amazing! Pick up the DELUXE HOPES AND FEARS too! Long live the KEANE!

reviewText: I bought two copies of this concert, one for my son, and one for a friend. When we tried to view them we found that the concerts don't play on any of my Bluray players. Beware, this appears to be a quality issue, and you don't want to get suckered into owning a malfunctioning disc. I will attempt to return these to Amazon for replacements that work.

reviewText: Speaking as a Keane fan, I can see no fault w/this DVD; The performances are right on(Tom, Tim & Richard in top form...), the sound amazing, the light/stage show energetic; The harmonies are pulled off flawlessly, and the energy of the live show only pushes the songs to a higher level. There are some nice surprises that are fitting, and this DVD only further demonstrates why Keane are one of the greatest pop rock bands out there. It's amazing all this sound comes from 3 guys. A must have for any fan, will watch and even just listen to over and over.
